  JOHANNESBURG - Several law firms and politicians are planning to take Eskom to court over the breach of obligation to provide electricity. Eskom's rolling blackouts have done enough damage to the already struggling economy. SA's Electricity crisis | Looming court battle over power cuts The power utility has until the end of the week to respond to a letter of demand calling for an end to load-shedding. Attorney Siphile Buthelezi explains above. #eNCA speaks to Mpumelelo Zikalala from Zikalala Attorneys.